[Woojong] How should we sort them?

00:31:47.302 --> 00:31:48.845
-[Jeongsu] Let's do it by time slots.
-Okay.

00:31:48.929 --> 00:31:49.930
I'll take ones at lunchtime.

00:31:50.013 --> 00:31:51.348
[Taejin] Another one for dinner.

00:31:51.431 --> 00:31:53.516
-Oh, wait. This one's lunch.
-Set it here.

00:31:54.309 --> 00:31:55.685
[Taejin] What about this?

00:31:55.769 --> 00:31:58.313
Hello, sir. By any chance,
do you know this guy?

00:31:58.396 --> 00:31:59.397
Yeah, I do.

00:31:59.481 --> 00:32:01.274
Do you have receipts
from when Taejoong covered...

00:32:01.358 --> 00:32:03.026
-Thank you so much.
-Yeah, no worries.

00:32:03.109 --> 00:32:04.110
-You get it?
-Yeah.

00:32:04.194 --> 00:32:05.695
-Nice. Good work.
-Found one.

00:32:05.779 --> 00:32:06.780
PETITION

00:32:06.863 --> 00:32:08.490
I appreciate you taking
the time to sign this.

00:32:08.573 --> 00:32:10.617
I was so shocked
when I first heard the news.

00:32:10.700 --> 00:32:13.536
-It's the least I could do for him.
-Thank you so much.

00:32:13.620 --> 00:32:14.704
[Daehoon] I couldn't find any.

00:32:14.788 --> 00:32:15.997
[Jeongsu] What was the time slot?

00:32:16.081 --> 00:32:17.123
-What about this?
-Papa Bread.

00:32:17.207 --> 00:32:18.250
-Put it here.
-Okay.

00:32:18.333 --> 00:32:20.001
TAEJOONG'S MOVEMENTS
ON THE DAY OF THE INCIDENT

00:32:20.085 --> 00:32:21.127
Here.

00:32:21.211 --> 00:32:23.171
We don't have anything from 2:00 to 2:30.

00:32:23.255 --> 00:32:25.340
-Yeah.
-[chatter continues]

00:32:25.423 --> 00:32:26.424
Nothing in my pile.

00:32:27.425 --> 00:32:29.511
-Strange.
-30 minutes.

00:32:29.594 --> 00:32:31.012
[groans softly]

00:32:31.096 --> 00:32:32.764
Try to remember, Hyung. Think.

00:32:32.847 --> 00:32:34.224
Wait, let me think.

00:32:34.307 --> 00:32:37.143
What was I doing... after the delivery?

00:32:37.978 --> 00:32:39.354
I remember. Okay, so...

00:32:39.437 --> 00:32:40.981
My bike suddenly had a problem.

00:32:41.606 --> 00:32:43.525
So after lunch, I had Kyungho fix it.

00:32:43.608 --> 00:32:44.901
Yeah, that should be it.

00:32:48.196 --> 00:32:49.572
-Look, there he is.
-Right.

00:32:49.656 --> 00:32:50.991
-That's his bike.
-Just like he said.

00:32:51.074 --> 00:32:52.784
Would you mind
if I take a picture of this?

00:32:52.867 --> 00:32:54.244
[laughing]

00:32:54.327 --> 00:32:55.829
A photo is not gonna be enough.

00:32:55.912 --> 00:32:58.290
I'll make you a copy
of the video, all right? Video is better.

00:32:58.373 --> 00:33:00.000
-[all] Thank you so much.
-We appreciate it.

00:33:00.083 --> 00:33:04.838
THE DAY BEFORE THE INCIDENT
THE DAY OF THE INCIDENT

00:33:04.921 --> 00:33:06.256
How on earth...

00:33:06.339 --> 00:33:07.966
[chuckles] I can't believe it.

00:33:08.049 --> 00:33:09.384
[chuckles softly]

00:33:10.927 --> 00:33:11.970
This is impressive.

00:33:12.053 --> 00:33:14.848
-[all laughing]
-Man, as we were doing this,

00:33:14.931 --> 00:33:17.642
it made me realize
how insanely hard he was working.

00:33:17.726 --> 00:33:20.020
I don't understand
how he never took a single break.

00:33:23.481 --> 00:33:26.484
With this kind of alibi,
we should be able to put up a good fight.

00:33:27.610 --> 00:33:29.779
Actually, I think we can win this.

00:33:30.989 --> 00:33:32.157
[all chuckle in relief]

00:33:38.121 --> 00:33:40.790
Would it be okay for me
to take some of this for the case?

00:33:40.874 --> 00:33:42.334
-Take whatever you need.
-Yes, of course.

00:33:42.417 --> 00:33:43.668
We can bring the rest to you later.

00:33:43.752 --> 00:33:44.753
Yeah.

00:33:45.295 --> 00:33:46.755
[Woojong] We got this.

00:33:47.881 --> 00:33:48.965
[Jeongsu] Great job, everyone.

00:33:49.049 --> 00:33:50.050
[Woojong] Yeah, you too.

00:33:50.550 --> 00:33:51.801
[Taejin] Thanks for helping, guys.

00:33:51.885 --> 00:33:53.678
-I mean it.
-[Woojong] Yeah, we got you.

00:33:54.262 --> 00:33:55.764
[cries softly]

00:33:56.389 --> 00:33:58.558
Why wouldn't you at least
eat a proper meal?

00:34:01.394 --> 00:34:02.896
[sniffles]

00:34:07.734 --> 00:34:09.444
COURT

00:34:11.780 --> 00:34:12.947
[bailiff] All rise.

00:34:24.459 --> 00:34:25.668
Please be seated.

00:34:30.965 --> 00:34:35.011
[judge] We will now begin
case number 2020-98374.

00:34:35.095 --> 00:34:39.057
The defendant, Park Taejoong
is being tried on the charges of murder,

00:34:39.140 --> 00:34:42.060
mutilation of a corpse,
and abandonment of a body.

00:34:44.729 --> 00:34:46.314
[lawyer] As you can see, the defendant,

00:34:46.398 --> 00:34:49.692
Park Taejoong, is an ordinary,
functioning member of society.

00:34:50.652 --> 00:34:52.779
I would say he lives a normal life.

00:34:54.114 --> 00:34:56.116
Also, it's clear from the petitions alone

00:34:56.199 --> 00:34:58.952
that he is held in high regard
by those around him.

00:34:59.703 --> 00:35:02.747
Finally, it is obvious when reviewing
the timeline of the defendant,

00:35:03.540 --> 00:35:05.500
that contrary to the prosecution's claim,

00:35:05.583 --> 00:35:08.336
it would be impossible for my client
to have committed the crime,

00:35:08.420 --> 00:35:10.964
dismember the victim
and dispose of the body.

00:35:12.048 --> 00:35:14.592
This is irrefutable proof
that he is innocent.

00:35:14.676 --> 00:35:15.885
I rest my case.

00:35:15.969 --> 00:35:17.846
[hushed chatter]

00:35:22.183 --> 00:35:23.893
Prosecution, you have the floor.

00:35:25.437 --> 00:35:27.814
Will the defendant please take a seat
at the witness stand?

00:35:33.194 --> 00:35:36.781
WITNESS STAND

00:35:40.827 --> 00:35:44.497
Right. So, similar to the defense,
we also followed the defendant's actions

00:35:44.581 --> 00:35:46.624
and movements on the day of the incident.

00:35:47.709 --> 00:35:50.670
This is the GPS tracking data
of the defendant's whereabouts

00:35:50.754 --> 00:35:52.338
down to the second.

00:35:52.422 --> 00:35:53.923
And, as you can see,

00:35:54.007 --> 00:35:56.259
they match the timeline
presented by the defense.

00:35:57.010 --> 00:35:59.304
So I have no objection
to the fact that the defendant

00:35:59.387 --> 00:36:01.264
is a hardworking and sincere person.

00:36:01.347 --> 00:36:03.975
In Article 27 of our Constitution,

00:36:04.058 --> 00:36:05.059
in paragraph four,

00:36:05.143 --> 00:36:08.104
it states that the accused
is innocent until proven guilty,

00:36:08.188 --> 00:36:10.690
and when in doubt,
judgment favors the defendant.

00:36:11.524 --> 00:36:14.903
Personally, I sincerely hope
that Park Taejoong is innocent.

00:36:14.986 --> 00:36:16.863
I truly want to believe that.

00:36:17.697 --> 00:36:19.741
However, there are issues that trouble me.

00:36:19.824 --> 00:36:22.118
And if the defendant
could clear a few things up,

00:36:22.202 --> 00:36:23.495
I'm sure we would all appreciate it.

00:36:23.578 --> 00:36:24.746
Is that all right with you?

00:36:26.790 --> 00:36:27.791
Yes.

00:36:30.168 --> 00:36:32.086
Now, here's my first point of concern.

00:36:32.962 --> 00:36:34.005
The records show

00:36:34.088 --> 00:36:37.008
that the defendant made
a delivery to the victim's residence.

00:36:38.927 --> 00:36:42.555
Of course, delivering to the victim's home
could be completely random,

00:36:42.639 --> 00:36:44.682
especially since she lived
in the same district.

00:36:45.225 --> 00:36:47.811
But it's the timeline of it
that confuses me.

00:36:48.561 --> 00:36:51.689
From the time he arrived,
to the time he departed her home,

00:36:51.773 --> 00:36:55.652
the duration of the delivery
was approximately seven minutes in total.

00:36:55.735 --> 00:36:56.945
If you look here,

00:36:57.028 --> 00:36:59.656
it was marked as a contactless delivery
to the third floor.

00:37:01.825 --> 00:37:04.410
But isn't seven minutes
a little long for that?

00:37:09.249 --> 00:37:11.042
[elevator bell dings]

00:37:11.125 --> 00:37:12.293
[panting]

00:37:12.377 --> 00:37:13.545
[camera shutter clicks]

00:37:24.097 --> 00:37:25.348
Well, that's because...

00:37:26.057 --> 00:37:27.267
I had to take care of a tree.

00:37:27.350 --> 00:37:28.726
Could you be more specific?

00:37:28.810 --> 00:37:30.144
Uh, yes.

00:37:30.228 --> 00:37:32.480
it was a China doll tree.

00:37:32.564 --> 00:37:34.065
It's considered a partial shade plant,

00:37:34.148 --> 00:37:36.234
meaning they shouldn't
get too much sunlight.

00:37:36.317 --> 00:37:39.362
As I was leaving, I saw that
it was placed in front of the window.

00:37:39.445 --> 00:37:42.073
I couldn't help myself,
so I moved it into the shade

00:37:42.156 --> 00:37:43.992
and left some tips for the owner.

00:37:45.285 --> 00:37:48.162
That might be why it took me so long.
I left after that.

00:37:48.246 --> 00:37:49.873
Hmm, I see.

00:37:49.956 --> 00:37:51.124
Understood.

00:37:51.207 --> 00:37:52.625
Moving on to the next question.

00:37:53.668 --> 00:37:55.920
While tracking the defendant's movements,

00:37:57.130 --> 00:37:59.132
we found this security footage.

00:37:59.215 --> 00:38:00.675
Could you explain this for us?

00:38:00.758 --> 00:38:02.135
EXHIBIT VIDEO 1) DEFENDANT'S MOVEMENTS

00:38:02.218 --> 00:38:05.013
Excuse me, young man.
Could you lend a hand?

00:38:07.432 --> 00:38:08.683
I was just...

00:38:08.766 --> 00:38:11.102
I finished delivering jokbal
to a customer.

00:38:11.185 --> 00:38:14.105
When I came back, I helped
an old woman with her suitcase.

00:38:14.856 --> 00:38:16.232
So I did what anyone would do

00:38:16.316 --> 00:38:18.276
and helped her
move her things up the hill.

00:38:24.157 --> 00:38:26.826
By any chance... was it this suitcase?

00:38:27.702 --> 00:38:28.786
[Taejoong] Yes, looks like it.

00:38:30.496 --> 00:38:31.915
[prosecutor] That's strange.

00:38:31.998 --> 00:38:33.416
Because this suitcase...

00:38:34.792 --> 00:38:37.962
was found near the location
of where the body was discovered.

00:38:38.046 --> 00:38:39.881
[hushed chatter]

00:38:39.964 --> 00:38:42.216
Forensic analysis confirmed
that this suitcase

00:38:42.300 --> 00:38:44.302
was used to transport
the dismembered body.

00:38:44.385 --> 00:38:45.511
Objection.

00:38:45.595 --> 00:38:46.596
Right, I agree.

00:38:47.388 --> 00:38:49.807
Just because the suitcase
appears to be the same model,

00:38:49.891 --> 00:38:52.644
it doesn't prove that it was
the exact one used in the crime.

00:38:52.727 --> 00:38:55.355
Also... we checked all the footage

00:38:55.438 --> 00:38:59.233
and we only found a single video clip
of the defendant with the suitcase.

00:39:00.026 --> 00:39:02.487
He doesn't appear
in any other location besides that.

00:39:02.570 --> 00:39:05.531
It's possible, you, unintentionally,
moved through the blind spots.

00:39:05.615 --> 00:39:06.783
The thing is...

00:39:06.866 --> 00:39:09.619
how can someone know
the location of every camera,

00:39:09.702 --> 00:39:12.205
unless they've gone through
these streets hundreds of times?

00:39:12.288 --> 00:39:14.207
[echoing] That would be impossible.

00:39:14.290 --> 00:39:16.626
So I actually support
the objection, Your Honor.

00:39:17.210 --> 00:39:19.379
Now, why were you
in possession of the victim's phone?

00:39:20.213 --> 00:39:21.506
No, I was...

00:39:21.589 --> 00:39:24.842
The elderly lady asked me
to help carry her things, so I...

00:39:25.635 --> 00:39:26.761
[prosecutor] Mr. Park Taejoong?

00:39:27.512 --> 00:39:29.889
Why was the victim's phone
in your possession?

00:39:32.433 --> 00:39:33.434
The phone? Uh...

00:39:34.477 --> 00:39:36.437
I couldn't have had
the victim's phone, sir.

00:39:37.522 --> 00:39:38.523
Is that right?

00:39:41.317 --> 00:39:46.322
EXHIBIT VIDEO 2)
DEFENDANT SEEN HOLDING THE VICTIM'S PHONE

00:39:47.615 --> 00:39:49.659
[hushed chatter]

00:40:03.256 --> 00:40:04.340
So that was...

00:40:05.299 --> 00:40:06.718
I was... just...

00:40:07.301 --> 00:40:09.887
I was eating... and I heard
the phone ring behind me, so...

00:40:09.971 --> 00:40:13.391
I answered it, and then
I headed out to return it right away.

00:40:16.769 --> 00:40:17.770
Where'd you return it?

00:40:18.896 --> 00:40:20.106
Was it here?

00:40:21.733 --> 00:40:22.734
Yes, that's right.

00:40:23.276 --> 00:40:26.112
And actually,
they offered a reward for it.

00:40:28.823 --> 00:40:30.450
CONVENIENCE STORE CCTV

00:40:30.533 --> 00:40:34.203
So who did you return the phone to
if it wasn't the victim?

00:40:35.496 --> 00:40:39.125
And why was her body
less than 40 meters away?

00:40:41.502 --> 00:40:42.879
I don't know, because I never...

00:40:44.422 --> 00:40:46.090
I didn't actually meet her.

00:40:46.174 --> 00:40:48.217
She said she didn't want
a stranger to know where--

00:40:48.301 --> 00:40:49.552
Defendant...

00:40:50.219 --> 00:40:52.305
-Why do you keep lying to me?
-I'm not.

00:40:52.388 --> 00:40:54.891
No, I swear I'm telling you the truth.

00:40:56.642 --> 00:40:57.810
[prosecutor exhales sharply]

00:40:59.812 --> 00:41:01.314
[sighs]

00:41:01.397 --> 00:41:03.941
Now what you see
on the screen are the coordinates

00:41:04.025 --> 00:41:05.860
from the GPS data of the victim's phone.

00:41:06.402 --> 00:41:09.781
They almost match the movements
of the defendant perfectly.

00:41:09.864 --> 00:41:12.033
Do you have some
explanation for this, too?

00:41:12.116 --> 00:41:13.242
Because you just said...

00:41:14.035 --> 00:41:15.203
that you returned it,

00:41:15.286 --> 00:41:17.914
and yet it's obvious
that you had it with you all day.

00:41:18.790 --> 00:41:20.416
[sighs in exasperation]

00:41:20.500 --> 00:41:23.127
I really don't know
how to explain any of that.

00:41:23.211 --> 00:41:24.295
You don't know?

00:41:24.378 --> 00:41:26.089
Maybe this will jog your memory.

00:41:27.340 --> 00:41:29.050
During our investigation,

00:41:29.133 --> 00:41:31.969
we conducted a forensic examination
at the site of the murder.

00:41:32.053 --> 00:41:34.347
But due to the complex
nature of the crimes,

00:41:34.430 --> 00:41:37.225
we did not receive the results
until earlier today.

00:41:37.308 --> 00:41:39.060
[lawyer] Objection!

00:41:39.143 --> 00:41:41.229
This evidence was not disclosed
during discovery.

00:41:41.312 --> 00:41:42.605
Please strike it.

00:41:43.898 --> 00:41:44.941
Overruled.

00:41:45.024 --> 00:41:46.526
-You may proceed.
-Right.

00:41:48.194 --> 00:41:49.195
Mr. Park.

00:41:49.946 --> 00:41:51.447
I still want to be on your side.

00:41:51.531 --> 00:41:53.658
But all the evidence
keeps pointing to you.

00:41:57.120 --> 00:41:59.080
LIKELY LOCATION OF THE MURDER

00:41:59.163 --> 00:42:01.124
[crowd gasping and murmuring]

00:42:01.958 --> 00:42:05.294
The victim was discovered in the bathroom
of a vacant unit on another floor

00:42:05.378 --> 00:42:07.213
somewhere else in the building.

00:42:07.296 --> 00:42:09.841
Brutally murdered,
then dismembered by the culprit

00:42:09.924 --> 00:42:10.967
with no remorse.

00:42:11.050 --> 00:42:13.136
The prosecution believes
that the perpetrator

00:42:13.219 --> 00:42:15.805
placed her lifeless body in warm water

00:42:15.888 --> 00:42:18.349
in order to manipulate the time of death.

00:42:18.432 --> 00:42:21.435
Furthermore, bodily fluids
presumed to belong to the culprit

00:42:21.519 --> 00:42:23.563
were found inside the victim's body.

00:42:23.646 --> 00:42:25.273
[murmuring continues]

00:42:35.783 --> 00:42:37.535
[panicked breathing]

00:42:44.208 --> 00:42:46.085
[prosecutor] If you would be so kind
as to read aloud

00:42:46.169 --> 00:42:48.504
whose semen was identified in the report?

00:42:49.547 --> 00:42:51.048
[hushed chatter]

00:42:59.265 --> 00:43:00.600
This can't...

00:43:00.683 --> 00:43:02.977
PARK TAEJOONG, VICTIM'S EVIDENCE SAMPLE

00:43:05.313 --> 00:43:07.690
[prosecutor] You said you spent
seven minutes caring for a plant.

00:43:07.773 --> 00:43:09.984
Sure you weren't filling
the bathtub with warm water?

00:43:10.067 --> 00:43:12.195
It seems like that would have
taken seven minutes.

00:43:12.278 --> 00:43:13.279
[Taejoong] I...

00:43:14.864 --> 00:43:16.699
It... It wasn't me.

00:43:17.783 --> 00:43:19.160
I didn't do it.

00:43:21.204 --> 00:43:22.580
I swear I didn't do it!

00:43:22.663 --> 00:43:23.873
[prosecutor] Mr. Park...

00:43:23.956 --> 00:43:27.543
If you feel even the slightest bit
of guilt toward the victim,

00:43:27.627 --> 00:43:29.754
you could at least tell us why you did it.

00:43:30.338 --> 00:43:32.381
What did she do to deserve
such a horrific death?

00:43:32.465 --> 00:43:34.217
No, Suji. I didn't.

00:43:34.300 --> 00:43:36.302
[crowd murmuring]

00:43:38.971 --> 00:43:41.224
Sir, please listen to me. I'm innocent.

00:43:41.307 --> 00:43:43.434
It wasn't me, I swear!

00:43:43.517 --> 00:43:44.936
-I didn't kill her!
-Maintain order.

00:43:45.019 --> 00:43:47.271
-Your Honor, you have to believe me.
-Sit down, defendant.

00:43:47.355 --> 00:43:49.065
It's not me. I didn't do it!

00:43:49.148 --> 00:43:51.567
I... Wait, wait! Let go of me!

00:43:52.401 --> 00:43:54.362
Your Honor, I'm begging you.

00:43:54.445 --> 00:43:56.239
Please, believe me. [whimpers]

00:43:56.322 --> 00:43:58.074
Oh, also...

00:43:58.741 --> 00:43:59.909
That tree that you mentioned...

00:44:00.785 --> 00:44:02.662
We asked the tenants about it,

00:44:02.745 --> 00:44:05.039
and not a single one of them
had ever seen it.

00:44:05.122 --> 00:44:06.958
Perhaps this was just your imagination.

00:44:07.625 --> 00:44:09.335
Your Honor. No, wait.

00:44:09.418 --> 00:44:10.878
I swear I'm telling the truth!

00:44:10.962 --> 00:44:12.338
Let go! Wait!

00:44:12.421 --> 00:44:13.589
It's not me!

00:44:13.673 --> 00:44:15.216
I didn't do it.

00:44:15.967 --> 00:44:16.968
[gavel banging]

00:44:17.051 --> 00:44:18.511
[judge] Order! Order in the court!

00:44:19.720 --> 00:44:21.764
-Your Honor, it wasn't me!
-This court will recess.

00:44:28.437 --> 00:44:30.731
[imperceptible]

00:44:53.754 --> 00:44:54.964
I have bad news.

00:44:55.047 --> 00:44:56.382
Your lawyer quit.

00:44:57.508 --> 00:44:59.844
Taejin is doing his best
to look for a new one,

00:45:00.928 --> 00:45:02.138
but no luck so far.

00:45:04.849 --> 00:45:06.892
He said we had a real chance of winning.

00:45:08.477 --> 00:45:10.688
The sentencing hearing
is around the corner.

00:45:18.195 --> 00:45:19.196
Suji.

00:45:21.198 --> 00:45:22.199
I'm so sorry.

00:45:25.411 --> 00:45:26.746
I'm sorry for everything.

00:45:28.998 --> 00:45:30.541
Show me your right wrist, please.

00:45:31.250 --> 00:45:32.418
What?

